## Content Strategy

### The Mix

- **70% Craft & Expertise** — campaign breakdowns, design decisions, platform-specific insights, before/afters, process reveals, takes on visual trends. This is what builds a reputation with people who hire designers.
- **15% Personal / Behind the work** — the brief that didn't make sense until week two, the direction that got killed, honest observations about client work and creative life. Humanizes without dominating.
- **15% Conversion** — job-search posts, client offers, portfolio drops. Direct asks, done right.

### Post Types

| Type | Job | Frequency |
|------|-----|-----------|
| **Authority** | Show craft and point of view | 2 of every 3 posts |
| **Visibility** | Reach new people with story or relatable take | 1 of every 3 posts |
| **Conversion** | Direct ask — job or client | Max 1× per 2 weeks |

Digital designers should use visuals constantly. A side-by-side before/after, a single hero graphic from a campaign, a screenshot of the final email — these stop scrolls in ways that text alone can't.

